:140px;object-fit:contain;background:#fff;border-radius:8px;\" loading=\"lazy\" />\n      <p style=\"margin:10px 0 4px 0;\"><strong>Best overall:</strong> #4 Lenovo 24&quot; FHD All-in-One Desktop Computer for Home &#038; Office</p>\n      <p style=\"margin:0 0 10px 0;font-size:14px;color:#555;\">the strongest rating/review combination in this comparison.</p>\n      <a href=\"https://www.amazon.com/dp/B0GY23R666?tag=skymaxx0e-20\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer sponsored\" style=\"background:#8920F3;color:#fff;padding:10px 18px;border-radius:6px;text-decoration:none;font-weight:600;display:inline-block;\">Buy on Amazon USA &rarr;</a>\n    </div>\n    <div style=\"flex:1;min-width:220px;background:#fff;border-radius:10px;padding:16px;text-align:center;\">\n      <img decoding=\"async\" src=\"/images/img-28.jpg\" alt=\"Lenovo IdeaCentre All-in-One Desktop Computer, 24&quot; FHD Anti-Glare IPS Display, 8GB RAM, 512GB PCIe SSD, Intel 4-Core Processor, Wi-Fi 6, Bluetooth 5.2, Windows 11 Home, Everyday Use AIO\" style=\"width:140px;height:140px;object-fit:contain;background:#fff;border-radius:8px;\" loading=\"lazy\" />\n      <p style=\"margin:10px 0 4px 0;\"><strong>Best value / budget pick:</strong> #3 Lenovo IdeaCentre All-in-One Desktop Computer</p>\n      <p style=\"margin:0 0 10px 0;font-size:14px;color:#555;\">the lowest price point among the options compared.</p>\n      <a href=\"https://www.amazon.com/dp/B0GYRSHB2F?tag=skymaxx0e-20\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer sponsored\" style=\"background:#8920F3;color:#fff;padding:10px 18px;border-radius:6px;text-decoration:none;font-weight:600;display:inline-block;\">Buy on Amazon USA &rarr;</a>\n    </div>\n  </div>\n  <p style=\"margin-bottom:0;\">If you&#8217;re unsure, the top-rated pick is the lower-risk choice; the budget pick is reasonable if price is your primary constraint.</p>\n</div>\n\n<div style=\"margin:24px 0;\">\n<h3 style=\"margin-top:0;\">Frequently Asked Questions</h3>\n<div style=\"display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:12px;\">\n<div style=\"background:#f9f9fb;border-radius:10px;padding:16px;\">\n<p style=\"margin:0 0 6px 0;font-weight:600;color:#290342;\">What’s the main advantage of an all-in-one over a regular desktop tower?</p>\n<p style=\"margin:0;color:#333;\">Everything - the computer, monitor, and speakers - is built into one unit, which saves desk space and cable clutter. The trade-off is that upgrading components later (especially the graphics card) is usually impossible or very limited compared to a tower.</p>\n</div>\n<div style=\"background:#f9f9fb;border-radius:10px;padding:16px;\">\n<p style=\"margin:0 0 6px 0;font-weight:600;color:#290342;\">Can I upgrade the RAM or storage in an all-in-one PC later?</p>\n<p style=\"margin:0;color:#333;\">Some models have an accessible panel for RAM/storage upgrades, but many, especially slimmer designs, solder components directly to the board. Check the specific model’s specifications or manual before buying if future upgrades matter to you.</p>\n</div>\n<div style=\"background:#f9f9fb;border-radius:10px;padding:16px;\">\n<p style=\"margin:0 0 6px 0;font-weight:600;color:#290342;\">Are all-in-one PCs good for gaming?</p>\n<p style=\"margin:0;color:#333;\">Most all-in-ones use integrated or entry-level graphics meant for office work, web browsing, and media - they can run light or older games but aren’t built for demanding modern titles the way a gaming desktop or laptop with a dedicated GPU is.</p>\n</div>\n<div style=\"background:#f9f9fb;border-radius:10px;padding:16px;\">\n<p style=\"margin:0 0 6px 0;font-weight:600;color:#290342;\">What screen size and resolution should I look for?</p>\n<p style=\"margin:0;color:#333;\">21-24\" at 1080p suits basic use, while 27\" at 1440p or higher gives more usable screen space for multitasking and photo/video work - match the size to your desk space since, unlike a monitor, you can’t swap it out separately later.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n"
